title: The Sorrows of a Show Girl
creator: Kenneth McGaffrey
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Sorrows of a Show Girl, by Kenneth McGaffrey. Originally printed in The Morning Telegraph in New York, this is the story of Miss Sabrina, the show girl, and her ups and downs with the unpredictable theatrical industry and the Great White Way, the lights and glamour of Broadway. "In order to set myself right with both the public and the vast army of Sabrinas that add youth and beauty to our stage, and brilliancy and gaiety to our well known cafes, I wish to say that she is all that she should be...”- Kenneth McGaffrey (Summary by Amanda Friday) Cast: Narrator: Chuck Williamson Sabrina: Amanda Friday Mr. Jenkins: Robert Hoffman Audio edited by Amanda Friday For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available

reviews.reviewbody: Wisecracking Broadway baby circa 1908. Amanda Friday, you were terrific! Very very well done. I was sorry when it ended.
